{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1940 |Team=Oregon State Beavers |Image= |ImageSize=200px |Conference=Pacific Coast Conference |ShortConference=PCC |APRank= |CoachRank= |Record=5-3-1 |ConfRecord=4-3-1 |HeadCoach=[[Lon Stiner]] |StadiumArena=[[Bell Field]] |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= }} {{1940 PCC football standings}} The '''1940 Oregon State Beavers football team''' represented [[Oregon State University|Oregon State College]] in the [[1940 college football season|1940 NCAA college football season]]. The Beavers ended this season with five wins, three losses, and one tie. The Beavers scored 128 points and allowed 80 points. The team was led by head coach Lon Stiner.
==Schedule== The Beavers finished the season with an 5&ndash;3&ndash;1 record, 4&ndash;3&ndash;1 in the Pacific Coast Conference. Ranks are based on the time the game was played.
